Job_URL: http://ABOUT US Card Kingdom is an online retailer that specializes in selling and buying Magic: The Gathering singles. Noted for their love of the community and game, Card Kingdom serves gamers all over the world. In addition to its eCommerce business, Card Kingdom owns and operates the award-winning game store and restaurant, Mox Boarding House, with locations in Seattle and Bellevue, and coming soon to Portland.  Card Kingdoms headquarters are located on Queen Anne, and just a short drive to Mox Seattle.  JOB DESCRIPTION Card Kingdom is looking for the first-ever UX/UI designer to join our eCommerce team. This role is responsible for creating intuitive and thoughtful UI wireframes / prototypes / flows from business requirements, while also being the voice of usability across both external and internal systems. They will also be responsible for creating highly-optimized production art assets, that are consistent with Card Kingdoms brand and appealing to our audience.  ROLE OBJECTIVES  Own the end-to-end design process and deliverables (including user personas, workflows, interactive wire-frames, mock-ups, and production art assets).  Work closely with our Agile sprint teams on the ever-changing requirements of our retail and online business.  Lead the planning and execution of consumer research at every stage of the product/feature lifecycle; from concept, prototype validations, all the way to usability tests on the final creation.  Balance your time and efforts across all the teams that need it - you ARE the design team!  Be future-looking with your designs but also understand the realities of shipping code.  Communicate complex, interactive design concepts clearly across different audiences and varying levels of the organization.  Understand how to utilize data to inform design decisions.  Empathize with the struggles of our users and be a customer advocate whether that is a customer ordering on their phone or an employee packing that same order.  QUALIFICATIONS  Bachelors Degree or 3+ years of related experience preferable.  Excellent communication, presentation, interpersonal and analytical skills.  Previous experience working with retail and/or online sales + fulfillment pipelines a plus.  Familiarity with A/B, multivariate, and other quantitative testing techniques.   An online portfolio or samples of work demonstrating experience creating great end-to-end, user- centered design solutions and patterns, across desktop and mobile devices.   Proficiency designing and prototyping with a variety of tools such as Photoshop, Illustrator, InDesign, Sketch Cloud, After Effects or similar.  Self-motivated, self-directed, with a positive outlook and can-do attitude. Our Benefits: Generous PTO policy, Excellent Health Benefit plans, 401k matching, Paid Holidays, Employee Discounts. Equal Opportunity Employment: We are committed to cultivating a workplace in which diverse perspectives and experiences are welcomed and respected. Job_URL: http://The CINC Product Team is looking for a UX designer interested in working across mobile experiences to define and deliver user-centered design solutions. You'll work as a dedicated member of a small, cross-functional team primarily responsible for prototyping, validating design solutions through discovery sessions, iterating solutions, and delivering development-ready specs and assets. Additionally, you will work off existing design documentation and collaborate with other design team members to build, maintain, and innovate a cohesive design system.  What will our UI/UX Designer do?   Work in a fast-paced and self-directed environment   Craft simple solutions to complex user problems with the ability to balance user and business needs   Work on a team with a dedicated product manager and a team of engineers to create a holistic, unified experience   Take full ownership of the product experience through the entire iterative lifecycle including ideation, design, discovery, implementation, and feedback   Conduct user research and usability testing to continuously improve the product, gain quick insights and help our users achieve their goals   Create prototypes using Sketch and InVision to convey the user journey   Help evolve our design language and the design culture at CINCExpected experience, skills, and qualities  Requirements:    You have relevant work experience or recent educational course completion   You are a team player who is willing to jump in and help when needed   You see failure as an opportunity to learn and generate better solutions based on a broader understanding   You are a fierce advocate of the user and utilize critical thinking  to create simple, easy-to-use interfaces   You have experience leading discovery or are an outgoing person who is comfortable speaking with users and stakeholders about their thoughts about experiences   You are organized, detail-oriented, and can juggle the needs of several projects to meet deadlines   You keep up with the latest design trends, patterns, and technologies, and can provide feedback and new ideas   You are familiar with mobile UX design and the unique design requirements for native iOS and Android applications.   You are familiar with Sketch and InVision and have experience creating user flows, wireframes, mockups, and clickable prototypes (Not required):   Experience with mobile UX design   Experience working from a style guide or centralized design system   Basic or introductory HTML, CSS, or JavaScriptCINC is an equal opportunity employer with a strong commitment to excellence through diversity.
